tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uteiravalondanu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teiravalon Danu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 1:07:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> Apologies ahead of time if this has been discussed before.  I've searched through the threads and not found anything on it to my liking.  Someone told me FoV did an indepth study on the subject?<br><br>What subject you ask.<br><br>Simple. It is my contention that the wurms and drakes in HoT and WToV are carbon copies of each other.  I was formerly on CoV faction and am recently moving over to Kael faction and have hunted in both wings of ToV.<br><br>Does anyone have any evidence that WToV mobs are harder than HoT mobs (more hp bigger AE --- both seemed exactly the same to me as I am a warrior and have tanked in both halls)<br><br>Please exclude boss mobs from discussion.<br><br><br>Second question what is the fewest people you have successfully seen WToV done with?<br><br>( This debate arose because I had done HoT with 6-8 and was told it could not be done in WToV cuz the mobs are harder.)<br><br>thanks ahead of time for your input.<br><br>later days-<br><br>Teiravalon<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 1:12:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> I've been on 2 group WToV armor farms.  There is also a guild on Brell that regularly does WToV with 12 or less people.  Never hunted in HoT so I can't compare.  But you can do WToV with a small crew. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usvenuce.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Svenuce</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://svenuce.homestead.com/files/blinky.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 1:23:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> I'm on COV faction (mostly) but have done a few WTOV raids in the past (about 3 months ago or so). <br><br>In my experience, the basic mobs in both halls are identical in terms of max damage, ae, etc. I can't definitively say whether one has more HPs than another but they seem to be about the same too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujdoe850.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jdoe850</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 1:30:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> So why in the hell do people opt for HoT armor? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvyper10.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vyper10</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 1:32:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> People opt for HoT armor because of faction concerns. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvaclavromanov.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vaclav Romanov</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 1:34:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> and for a number of classes there are pieces that are much better in HoT... plus the option of Dozekar items...<br><br>Hell, Furor from FoH uses Greaves of the Myrmidion...<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufendrylistalindir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fendryl Istalindir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 1:39:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> HoT - Everything can be pulled single; nothing runs; Gear tends to be more Stats/HP/Mana; CoV Faction for gear, but not gains/hits fighting here; CoV Faction = Benevolence Quests, HoT Quests, Movement in HoT, WW, etc.<br><br>WToV - Not as easilly single pullable; mobs run; Gear is more AC based; Gain Kael Faction while Fighting; First Broods &amp; WW Hunting w/o worrying about Faction Fixing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhubbestubbe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HubbeStubbe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 1:40:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> We do it because its more of a stats/resist gear choice and more convenient. Besides, its a natural choice since we where doing kael arena before.. Getting the entire guild to change faction is a pain. :P <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhubbestubbe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HubbeStubbe</A> at: 3/11/02 1:46:07 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uheka01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Heka01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 1:44:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> Having been in a CoV and now Factionless/Kael situation I can sum it up a bit.<br><br>Wurms are basically identical (West vs East Halls), APART from the fact in West they tend to gate more and run so need snares.<br><br>I too have done HoT with 6-8 people, West takes more due to the mobs being closer together, a few more roamer/longer pathing types and the runner phenomenon, West mobs also have a tendancy to warp more and maybe thats down to the wall geography, most HoT fights are on that 1st platform and the walls dont seem to be warp fest inducing like some of West ones are.<br><br>On the subject of the actual armours the Shrine quests tend to have lower AC but higher stats/HP/resists than their Kael equivalent so overall is arguably better in certain situations and classes.<br><br>Stikka Barbie Assassin<br>Mortalis<br>Antonius Bayle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ughitming.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ghitming</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 2:08:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> Wwing is much tougher if your Raid isn't beefy.  Not only are the mobs harder to split, the makeup is much different.<br><br>HoT has Racnars (wimps and no AE,) SK drakes, Rogue Drakes, and Ranger Drakes.  HoT also has no wandering Wurms, and the only time you see 2 Wurms together is in the pit.<br><br>WW has several juctions with multiple wurms, some of which are wanderers that got stuck.  Although they are easily split by Sneak Pulling, sometimes the wanderers will path/warp separately to a poorly positioned raid.  <br><br>Also, unless a WW Raid COHs in, they are stuck killing the first 8 mobs which have a much lower drop rate.<br><br>HoT is about 50 percent easier imo.<br><br>Ghitming<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uteiravalondanu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teiravalon Danu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 2:31:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> So it sounds like the mobs are identical but the pathing and pulls and locality of the Mobs in WToV makes it harder than HoT.<br><br><br>Sound like a good summarization?<br><br>thanks<br><br>Teiravalon <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uqalarrubican.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qalar Rubican</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 2:46:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> Bring a larger raid for WToV and since there are almost unlimited mobs to kill, you'll never clear it(unlike HoT). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uutari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Utari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 2:55:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> Small groups in WToV are tremendously inefficient.  Just because taking 6 people to WToV is possible doesn't make it worthwhile.  The hard to split mobs, doubled up wurms, and wandering wurms make it a nightmare for a small group.  Not to mention warping mobs, drakes running up the ledge to the hub, and pain in the ass CR.  Adding one group adds about 150% to the overall effort and adding a 3rd group brings it up even farther.  Its not that it isn't possible, its whether or not its worth it.<br><br>Soltari <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uteiravalondanu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teiravalon Danu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 5:20:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> Good point solwene.<br><br>I just wanted to make sure the mobs were the same. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukalran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 6:52:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> People have pointed out that the mobs aren't the same.   W ToV mobs gate, run and all have AE spells.  While you get some of the same mobs in HoT, you also get easier mobs.  It's the gating, warping, multi-pulling and non-stop AE that makes West Wing tougher, not the hp/damage output of the mobs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uraemius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raemius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 8:31:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> How would one go about sneak splitting/pulling the wurms?  I have worked with sneak before and havent had much sucess with the method.<br><br>The warp factor of these would make splitting quite difficult.  I do HoT currently and dont really face such problems.  When we move on to Wwing I'd like to be ready.<br><br>Please elaborate a little more for those of us unfamilair with this method <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Thanks,<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umurrdurr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Murr Durr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 8:39:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> Yea, from recent AOW killings a lot of the guild has good COV faction so we've been doing weekend HOT farms for new people/older members who want to switch to SS armor.  I was wearing deceivers and just completed my skyshrine set(arms/bp/legs, in my case) which I prefer over deceivers a good bit.  More hp, better stats..who cares about AC these days..<br>Having been a Kael faction guild for so long, HoT seems like such cake after West/central tov armor farms, and drop rates seem much higher, but it has been awhile since we did WTOV (read: Before AAXP~) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucoray.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Coray</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 9:07:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> There are only a few places where any tricks are required to split wurms in west, in fact only one place where i dont know of a way other than with a monk (the 2 in front of telkorenar).<br><br>Otherwise like most areas its simply a matter of being patient and/or pulling things in the correct order.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubroddathep.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brodda Thep</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 9:17:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> The biggest factors that cause people to prefer HoT over WW has been summed up pretty well.  You are more likely to get adds in West Wing.  You will have difficulty CRing.  You either need a CoV faction mage to COH in or you must take 6-8 entrance mobs that do not drop anything.<br><br>The worst thing about WW is the roaming wurms.  These don't walk around they warp around, so everythign will be clear and then the next second you are getting trounced.  <br><br>However, I think things would be a bit different if, from the very beginning, they made it so that west wing wurms didn't run.  I remember working that wing when they did run after getting low on health and that is an absolute nightmare.  Very very easy to wipe even with large numbers of people.  Luckily, that isn't the case anymore. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ughitming.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ghitming</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 11:11:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10225.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT vs WToV</span><hr size=1> Sneak pulling is using a long range weapon + Sneak + LOS to split mobs that are close.  Kendrick has a nice write up on it somewhere.  I learned it from his teachings over 2 years ago.  <br><br>I probably use it as often as I Feign split.  It feels like there is more art to it.<br><br>Ghitming<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><s